BEGIN:VTODO
UID:TODO-43850BB6-CB2E-427D-9894-BEFA86314E37
DTSTAMP:20260401T043907Z
SUMMARY:Write letter for Tapiwa
DESCRIPTION:The nomination package should include:\n1. The name of the facu
 lty member with whom the student will be\n   conducting research\; Harry B
 ermudez and Todd Emrick\n2. Why funding is not available for this student 
 during the summer\;\n   Tapiwa is a first-year graduate student in Polymer
  Science and\n   Engineering working on a new collaborative endeavor betwe
 en two\n   research groups.  While both Emrick and Bermudez have submitted
 \n   proposals to support Tapiwa\, and continue to do so\, currently there
 \n   is no funding available to cover the summer period.  This\n   assista
 ntship will help bridge the present funding gap.\n3. How the student shows
  commitment to increasing equity and\n   representation in their disciplin
 e\; As a native African\, Tapiwa has\n   very visibly represented the Poly
 mer Science department as a\n   Senator in the Graduate Student Government
  (GSG).  He has advocated\n   on behalf of all students\, notably within G
 SG having accomplished a\n   reduction in the graduate student fee for the
  Rec Center.  Ongoing\n   efforts within GSG include working to increase t
 he minimum wage for\n   Master's students.  Tapiwa regularly provides comm
 unity updates\n   about GSG activities through email and brief presentatio
 ns at our\n   Departmental Town Hall events.\n4. A description of the stud
 ent's strengths\; Tapiwa has a warm and\n   outgoing personality\, always 
 welcoming individuals in our community\n   by name.  He is one of those pe
 ople who brighten a room when they\n   enter.  Academically\, he has dived
  fearlessly into his first year\n   as a graduate student by balancing cou
 rsework\, research\, and a\n   leadership role as Departmental Senator in 
 the GSG.\n5. A copy of the student's CV.
CATEGORIES:AssocDH
SEQUENCE:1
PRIORITY:5
STATUS:NEEDS-ACTION
END:VTODO
